Titolo: Lost Tomb

Anno: 1982

Descrizione: Lost Tomb is an overhead-view multidirectional shooter written by Dan Lee and released in arcades by Stern Electronics in 1982. Armed with a gun and whip, the player uses dual joystick controls to explore the chambers of a South American pyramid looking for treasure and fighting off mummies and other occupants. The game was Stern's first arcade conversion kit and was intended for use with earlier titles from the company.In 1984, Datasoft published home ports for the Apple II, Atari 8-bit family, Commodore 64, and, as a self-booting disk, IBM PC compatibles.